{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"38631d82-0ef9-45c3-a9cb-5cb99f9cf98e","content":"Here's the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test \\\n  --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\nEverything after `--` is forwarded to the new test runner. You'll also need these NuGet packages in your test projects:\n\n| Old VSTest feature | New package |\n|-|-|\n| `--logger trx` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump` |\n\nAnd enable the new runner in your test `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n```\n\n> **Note:** The `--filter` syntax stays on the `dotnet test` side (before `--`) since it's handled at the orchestration level.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f102a85f-1865-4e1f-9b80-3d99d88a543d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing tooling migration, not a codebase task.\n\nLet me provide the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n\nKey differences when moving to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n1. `dotnet test` still works but the underlying runner changes\n2. Filter syntax changes from `--filter` to `--filter` (similar but may need adjustment)\n3. `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`\n4. Code coverage collection changes\n\n\n5. Blame options like `--blame-crash` and `--blame-hang` have different implementations\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform, you can still use `dotnet test` as the entry point, though some command-line options shift—particularly around reporting formats and extensions that need separate NuGet packages for features like TRX output and code coverage collection.\n\nFor .NET 8 with Microsoft.Testing.Platform, I need to add the appropriate extension packages to the test project to enable these features...\n\nActually, let me clarify the command syntax. With `dotnet test`, the platform-specific options get passed after the `--` separator, so `--report-trx`, `--coverage`, `--crashdump`, and `--hangdump` all go there. The filter syntax stays the same, but I should note that Microsoft.Testing.Platform may handle filter expressions differently depending on which test framework is being used. I need to clarify the approach for .NET 8 versus newer versions, since the argument passing differs depending on whether the testing platform is natively integrated or requires the `--` separator.","outputTokens":1233,"requestId":"CFE1:18DC54:5CBE79D:6800DE3:69EC0EEC"},"id":"317e099d-4ddd-4942-861b-ff657b7aa1db","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:46:59.167Z","parentId":"b993640e-29f2-44fd-8104-cc01f031b6ea"}
